Definition.WordDefinition: corncob \corn"cob`\ (k[^o]rn"k[o^]b`), n. The cob or axis on which the kernels of Indian corn grow. [U.S.] [1913 Webster]
corncob n : the hard cylindrical core that bears the kernels of an ear of corn
